# Model vs Entity Separation

## Core principle
- **Domain class** → `domain/entity/`, plain Dart + `Equatable`, no JSON, no Freezed, no suffix
- **Model** → `data/models/`, extends domain class, `@JsonSerializable`, no Freezed

The domain never knows how data is serialized.
The model extends the domain class — a `RouteModel` IS a `Route`.

## File locations and naming

```
lib/src/features/routes/
  domain/
    entity/
      routes_route.dart          ← class Route extends Equatable
      routes_route_type.dart     ← class RouteType extends Equatable
  data/
    models/
      routes_route_model.dart    ← @JsonSerializable class RouteModel extends Route
```

- Domain class file: `<feature_name>_<name>.dart` — class `<Name>` (no suffix)
- Model file: `<feature_name>_<name>_model.dart` — class `<Name>Model`

## Domain class — Equatable, no Freezed, no JSON

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/features/routes/domain/entity/routes_route.dart
import 'package:equatable/equatable.dart';

class Route extends Equatable {
  final String id;
  final String title;
  final String description;
  final double distanceKm;
  final int durationMinutes;
  final RouteType type;

  const Route({
    required this.id,
    required this.title,
    required this.description,
    required this.distanceKm,
    required this.durationMinutes,
    required this.type,
  });

  @override
  List<Object?> get props => [id, title, description, distanceKm, durationMinutes, type];
}

// ❌ BAD
class RouteEntity extends Equatable { ... }  // Entity suffix
class Route {                                 // No Equatable — equality broken
  @override bool operator ==(Object other) => ...  // manual equality, skip Equatable

@freezed abstract class Route with _$Route { ... } // Freezed on entity — forbidden
```

## Data Model — extends domain class, json_serializable, no Freezed

Model extends the entity, so `RouteModel` satisfies `Route` everywhere — no `toEntity()` needed.
`fromEntity()` IS required as a named constructor for write-back scenarios (POST/PUT to API).

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/features/routes/data/models/routes_route_model.dart
import 'package:json_annotation/json_annotation.dart';
import 'package:mobile_app/src/features/routes/domain/entity/routes_route.dart';

part 'routes_route_model.g.dart';

@JsonSerializable()
class RouteModel extends Route {
  const RouteModel({
    required super.id,
    required super.title,
    required super.description,
    @JsonKey(name: 'distance_km') required super.distanceKm,
    @JsonKey(name: 'duration_minutes') required super.durationMinutes,
    required super.type,
  });

  // ── Deserialization ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  factory RouteModel.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) =>
      _$RouteModelFromJson(json);

  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => _$RouteModelToJson(this);

  // ── Entity conversion ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  /// Creates a model from a domain object (used when writing back to API).
  factory RouteModel.fromEntity(Route route) => RouteModel(
        id: route.id,
        title: route.title,
        description: route.description,
        distanceKm: route.distanceKm,
        durationMinutes: route.durationMinutes,
        type: route.type,
      );
}

// ❌ BAD
@freezed abstract class RouteModel with _$RouteModel { ... }  // No Freezed on models
class RouteModel {                                             // Doesn't extend domain class
  final String id;
  RouteModel.fromEntity(Route r) { ... }                      // fromEntity outside class body
```

## Repository: no .toEntity() needed
Since `RouteModel extends Route`, the repository returns `RouteModel` typed as `Route` — no conversion method needed.
Use `RouteModel.fromEntity(route)` when serializing a domain object for a write (POST/PUT) request.

## Strict rules summary

| Rule | Domain class | Model |
|------|-------------|-------|
| Location | `domain/entity/` | `data/models/` |
| Class suffix | ❌ None (no `Entity`) | ✅ `Model` |
| Extends | `Equatable` | Domain class (e.g. `Route`) |
| Freezed | ❌ Never | ❌ Never |
| `Equatable` + `props` | ✅ Always | inherited from domain class |
| `fromJson` / `toJson` | ❌ Never | ✅ Always |
| `@JsonKey` | ❌ Never | ✅ Allowed |
| `fromEntity()` constructor | ❌ Never | ✅ Named constructor inside model |
| `toEntity()` method | not needed — model IS domain class | — |
| Imported by BLoC / UseCase | ✅ Domain class only | ❌ Never |
